						 <p>After Hector was slain, his corpse was fastened to a chariot and dragged around the walls of Troy. His loved ones could do nothing but look on in horror&#8230;</p> <p>But later his body was returned to his grieving father. I doubt our Achilles has any intention of releasing this corpse.</p> 
